WEBVTT

C01
00:00:03.670 --> 00:00:09.855
Open Lab, choose New agent, and start the guided creation flow.

C02
00:00:09.575 --> 00:00:17.817
Choose From prompt to describe the Agent directly, or From chats to include examples of the work it should handle.

C04
00:00:17.537 --> 00:00:27.159
This synthetic example starts with three chats: Acme has renewal blockers, Northstar is expanding, and the team needs a weekly account review. Add them with the Agent purpose.

C06
00:00:26.879 --> 00:00:36.819
Review the selected excerpts as examples. OpenPond turns their recurring goals, decisions, corrections, and answer patterns into the first Agent plan.

C07
00:00:36.539 --> 00:00:46.658
The draft converts those examples into the Agent's purpose, chat behavior, runnable actions, output formats, and Evals for your review.

C08
00:00:46.378 --> 00:00:52.652
The right side panel asks how the Agent should prioritize conflicting account risks.

C09
00:00:52.372 --> 00:01:00.753
Before creation, review the proposed name, chat endpoint, runnable actions, Evals, and output formats.

C09A
00:01:00.473 --> 00:01:09.071
If the plan misses a requirement, open Edit plan and describe the change in plain language before any Agent source is created.

C09B
00:01:08.791 --> 00:01:16.049
Review the revised plan, then click Confirm plan to create the Agent and run its Evals.

C10
00:01:15.769 --> 00:01:24.189
This is the creation result: OpenPond built the Agent and passed its behavior Evals against the Account Health examples.

C11
00:01:23.909 --> 00:01:31.346
After the Evals pass, the Agent is saved to your Profile and is ready to use.

C12
00:01:31.066 --> 00:01:37.658
The Agent page shows its purpose, chat entrypoint, and runnable account actions.
